    {
        "content": "<p>I've never heard of terminal connected, what's that?</p>",
        "id": 281606247,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Campion",
        "timestamp": 1652026142
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For essential geometric morphisms it's the property of the extra left adjoint preserving the terminal object, but there's an equivalent formulation in a paper of Osmond that works for arbitrary geometric morphisms, along the lines of the inverse image functor commuting with global sections morphisms (I'll dm you a link to that paper when I'm at my computer next week)</p>",
        "id": 281606453,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1652026419
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See section 5.3 here:<br>\n<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2108.12697.pdf\">https://arxiv.org/pdf/2108.12697.pdf</a></p>",
